 The Role
 Adobe seeks a Vice President, Information and Data Services (IDS) who will lead modernization of the companyâ€™s data platforms to support scale and enable continued growth of the business. Based in San Jose and reporting to the Chief Information Officer, Cynthia Stoddard, this individual will be responsible for the data and analytics strategy, data architecture, data governance and security, data platforms and applications supporting financial reporting critical to Adobeâ€™s business. S/he will collaborate with the CIO, leadership teams and relevant business functions including engineering to create robust capability roadmaps, build best-in-class analytics functionality, deploy self-service platforms, and drive delivery and implementation with quality, time-to-market, while maintaining high levels of reliability.
 The team is approximately 150 people who are based in the US and India.
 Additional responsibilities and expectations are highlighted below:
 Lead data and technology transformation
 Drive technology transformation  : Enable simplified processes and lead implementation of new solutions to enhance delivery speed and data products quality.
 Be a change champion  : Promote and practice a growth mindset to invigorate transformative initiatives and ensure successful implementation across teams.
